          <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Substance Use Disorder Coordination, Access, Recovery Enhancement Act of 2018 or the SUD CARE Act</b></p> <p>This bill increases the maximum number of patients that health care practitioners may initially treat with medication-assisted treatment (i.e., under a buprenorphine waiver), and also aligns federal privacy standards for substance use disorder patient records more closely with standards under the Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act.</p>]]></text>
        </item>
